The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 Zimbabwe players in currency row 

 - JANUARY 26 DIGEST 

 Durban: Top lawyer Beatrice Mtetwa is to advise Zimbabwes players in their bid to claim money they are owed by Zimbabwe Cricket (ZC). The players are seeking legal opinion over ZCs assertion that they should be paid in Zimbabwe currency, thats why we are talking to Mtetwa, player representative Clive Field said from Harare on Thursday. 

 Dubai: International Cricket Council on Thursday sent another coded message to the BCCI by claiming that 13 countries were keen to host a Twenty20 World Championship next year. 

Australia, Bermuda, Malaysia, New Zealand, South Africa, Sri Lanka, Thailand, United Arab Emirates and the West Indies have all indicated their desire to host the inaugural Twenty20 championship planned in late 2007 while England, Hong Kong, Nepal and Scotland have also expressed an interest in hosting future events, the ICC said in media release. The BCCI has firmly opposed the instant variety of the game. 

 Melbourne: Australias Olympic and world champion Ian Thorpe is planning to retire from swimming after the 2008 Beijing Olympics, aged 25, he told an Australian newspaper on Friday. 




